@node INST "How to install AClock"


Installing AClock is pretty simple, Copy AClock, AClock.info and AClock.guide
to your wbstartup and it will start automatically at boottime.

@endnode


@node WHAT "What is AClock?"


AClock is a receiver program for the DCF77 clock. AClock looks for the clock
data on the gameport or the parallelport depending on the setting of the
PORT @{"tooltype" link TOOL}. When AClock receives 2 valid minute informations it will
signal its main task to update the system and battery clock.

@endnode


@node TOOL "Changing the configuration."

AClock supports the following tooltypes:

 PORT         Where is the hardware connected?
              - JOY6 = pin  6 on game port 2
              - JOY4 = pin  4 on game port 2
              - JOY1 = pin  1 on game port 2
              - PAR  = pin 11 on parallel port
 WINX         X coordinate of AClocks window.
 WINY         Y coordinate of AClocks window.
 CX_POPUP     Popup the window on startup? (NO YES)
 CX_PRIORITY  Priority in the commodities chain.

@endnode


